				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ChardokB ~ Halls of Betrayal ?<a name="18320"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 1 04 7:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you're looking for beads, you have to kill the rabids that pop where there are &quot;ferocious&quot; chokidai.  The two places for those are (easiest to get to) in front of the castle and to the right of it (as you face it), and through the castle in an area they call the kennel (kind of outside area in back of the castle).
<br />

<br />
If you hunt at the entrance, you'll never see beads drop.  The rabids there drop the earring.  The rabids further in drop the Improved Healing IV cloak.  We went to try for some beads last night with 65 bard, 65 cleric, and 65 enchanter and were more than able to keep the spawns cleared.  Just don't die. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
And yes, the rabids are very rare now.  When the zone first opened, we were getting rabids often (two of us got beads in three hours and the common loot was rotting).  Last night, we cleared for 5 hours and saw two (both dropped common boots vs. beads).  Not sure if we'll try again.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
